257
00:14:09,109 --> 00:14:11,009
the closer you got to the edge of the cliff too,

258
00:14:11,009 --> 00:14:13,009
and the fire got bigger too,

259
00:14:13,009 --> 00:14:15,509
so it looked like something that was burning pass through there

260
00:14:15,509 --> 00:14:17,209
as it got bigger.

261
00:14:17,209 --> 00:14:19,309
Isn't that right, Miyuki?

262
00:14:19,309 --> 00:14:20,309
Yes.

263
00:14:20,309 --> 00:14:24,109
So the cursed demon dog...

264
00:14:24,109 --> 00:14:26,209
Does exist after all.

265
00:14:26,209 --> 00:14:27,909
Saki who fell from the cliff said,

266
00:14:27,909 --> 00:14:30,109
"Dog engulfed in flames" too.

267
00:14:30,109 --> 00:14:31,409
Idiot!

268
00:14:31,409 --> 00:14:34,309
There could be no such thing as a demon dog in this world!

269
00:14:34,309 --> 00:14:35,809
It's a trick!

270
00:14:35,809 --> 00:14:40,109
Somebody's just trying to make it look as if a demon dog exists!

271
00:14:40,109 --> 00:14:43,309
In order to put the blame on the demon dog for their crime.

272
00:14:43,309 --> 00:14:46,109
Exactly!

273
00:14:46,109 --> 00:14:47,609
I mean this is a time when the world is talking about

274
00:14:47,609 --> 00:14:49,209
TV broadcasts going digital,

275
00:14:49,209 --> 00:14:52,109
how can you possibly make us fuss over a demon dog?

276
00:14:52,109 --> 00:14:53,909
It's really making me "dizzy dear".

277
00:14:53,909 --> 00:14:56,109
Inspector Yamamura!

278
00:14:56,109 --> 00:15:01,709
Oh, did you catch on to the play on words I just mentioned?

279
00:15:01,709 --> 00:15:03,309
Who's this chum?

280
00:15:03,309 --> 00:15:05,209
He's an officer from the Gunma Prefectural Police Station,

281
00:15:05,209 --> 00:15:06,309
although he may not look it.

282
00:15:06,309 --> 00:15:09,109
So, this is Gunma Prefecture.

283
00:15:09,109 --> 00:15:10,909
And...

284
00:15:10,909 --> 00:15:13,309
how is Saki who fell off the cliff doing?

285
00:15:13,309 --> 00:15:17,809
Well, I heard that she was taken by ambulance to a hospital.

286
00:15:17,809 --> 00:15:19,909
That's our hospital.

287
00:15:19,909 --> 00:15:22,809
I got a call on my cell phone

288
00:15:22,809 --> 00:15:25,409
and was told she died in the ambulance.

289
00:15:25,409 --> 00:15:27,809
Oh, no.

290
00:15:27,809 --> 00:15:31,409
I don't know who's manipulating the demon dog

291
00:15:31,409 --> 00:15:32,609
but it's definite that somebody's

292
00:15:32,609 --> 00:15:35,009
picking a fight with the Inubushi family.

293
00:15:35,009 --> 00:15:38,309
That's true. Out of all the eight adopted children,

294
00:15:38,309 --> 00:15:41,209
half of us, four have already died.

295
00:15:41,209 --> 00:15:44,609
Then, for the time being, out of the four that now remain,

296
00:15:44,609 --> 00:15:48,209
will the three of you who are here give us your alibis?

297
00:15:48,209 --> 00:15:50,809
Tell us where and what you were doing around 19:00

298
00:15:50,809 --> 00:15:53,209
when Saki fell over the cliff.

299
00:15:53,209 --> 00:15:56,109
Miyuki has a concrete alibi because she was with us

300
00:15:56,109 --> 00:15:58,009
when we went to look at the grave of the dog

301
00:15:58,009 --> 00:16:00,609
located below the cliff!

302
00:16:00,609 --> 00:16:04,209
At about 19:00, I was taking a bath.

303
00:16:04,209 --> 00:16:07,009
Since Saki didn't come back for a while,

304
00:16:07,009 --> 00:16:09,009
I went outside to check on her.

305
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:12,309
She still loses her way a lot even now so...

306
00:16:12,309 --> 00:16:15,709
I was beside mother checking her body temperature,

307
00:16:15,709 --> 00:16:19,409
blood pressure and feeding her liquid food.

308
00:16:19,409 --> 00:16:21,909
Well, but since she's bed-ridden.

309
00:16:21,909 --> 00:16:25,809
I can't have her testify for me, though.

310
00:16:25,809 --> 00:16:27,209
As for you two,

311
00:16:27,209 --> 00:16:30,109
you don't seem to have anyone who can testify for you either.

312
00:16:30,109 --> 00:16:31,309
No.

313
00:16:31,309 --> 00:16:34,609
Normally there are three people helping me,

314
00:16:34,609 --> 00:16:37,409
but they've taken leave to visit their families.

315
00:16:37,409 --> 00:16:40,509
Mr. Mouri! It's the job of the police to ask that question!

316
00:16:40,509 --> 00:16:43,109
Please don't take my job away from me!

317
00:16:43,109 --> 00:16:46,809
Oh, isn't he a police officer?

318
00:16:46,809 --> 00:16:50,209
Oh, no. I lost the chance to introduce myself.

319
00:16:50,209 --> 00:16:53,209
His name is Kogoro Mouri.

320
00:16:53,209 --> 00:16:55,509
-Mou... -Mouri?

321
00:16:55,509 --> 00:16:56,809
Kogoro?

322
00:16:56,809 --> 00:16:59,909
Are you the renown Detective Kogoro Mouri?

323
00:16:59,909 --> 00:17:02,209
Yes, well...

324
00:17:02,209 --> 00:17:05,409
Huh? The atmosphere's changed.

325
00:17:05,409 --> 00:17:08,109
You just surprised us a bit.

326
00:17:08,109 --> 00:17:12,009
Before he left the house, the late Shinichi said...

327
00:17:12,009 --> 00:17:14,209
You'd better give yourselves up

328
00:17:14,209 --> 00:17:16,109
because he asked an acquaintance police officer to investigate

329
00:17:16,109 --> 00:17:17,609
and to solve the mystery

330
00:17:17,609 --> 00:17:20,109
of what is happening in the Inubushi family.

331
00:17:20,109 --> 00:17:22,309
But I had no idea that it was going to be

332
00:17:22,309 --> 00:17:25,609
the renown Sleeping Kogoro.

333
00:17:25,609 --> 00:17:28,909
Well, I'm the one who actually asked to investigate the incident.

334
00:17:28,909 --> 00:17:30,809
By the way, the day Shinichi

335
00:17:30,809 --> 00:17:33,409
was killed in his residence in Tokyo,

336
00:17:33,409 --> 00:17:37,409
I suppose there's no one here that went to Tokyo, is there?

337
00:17:37,409 --> 00:17:40,309
All four of us were in Tokyo.

338
00:17:42,109 --> 00:17:45,909
We went to persuade him to come back to the Inubushi family.

339
00:17:45,909 --> 00:17:49,409
It seemed that he suspected one of us,

340
00:17:49,409 --> 00:17:51,509
so we wanted to ask him why he thought so too.

341
00:17:51,509 --> 00:17:55,209
Well, but he was so afraid that he didn't tell us anything.

342
00:17:55,209 --> 00:17:59,709
It was as if he was saying that the culprit is among us.

343
00:17:59,709 --> 00:18:02,009
We heard about Shinichi's death

344
00:18:02,009 --> 00:18:04,609
as soon as we got back from Saki who we asked

345
00:18:04,609 --> 00:18:06,209
to keep watch over the answer phone.

346
00:18:06,209 --> 00:18:07,609
Which means that all four of you

347
00:18:07,609 --> 00:18:09,809
were together all the while you were in Tokyo?

348
00:18:09,809 --> 00:18:14,609
No. We all went together, but we all came back separately.

349
00:18:14,609 --> 00:18:17,709
By the way, isn't it about time you tell us

350
00:18:17,709 --> 00:18:21,009
about what you found out about Shinichi's case?

351
00:18:21,009 --> 00:18:23,909
You also mentioned that the accident of Keiji and Miwako

352
00:18:23,909 --> 00:18:25,709
that occurred previously had some connection

353
00:18:25,709 --> 00:18:27,709
with the chain of events that is happening too.

354
00:18:27,709 --> 00:18:30,309
We don't know yet if this has any connection to the incident,

355
00:18:30,309 --> 00:18:33,409
but Shinichi had the pearl that

356
00:18:33,409 --> 00:18:37,109
was on his necktie pin in his mouth!

357
00:18:39,109 --> 00:18:40,509
What seems to be the matter?

358
00:18:40,509 --> 00:18:46,809
Oh, nothing. There was one near Keiji who fell over the cliff like Saki.

359
00:18:46,809 --> 00:18:48,609
A pachinko ball.

360
00:18:48,609 --> 00:18:50,209
A pachinko ball?

361
00:18:50,209 --> 00:18:53,209
That old man used to love playing pachinko

362
00:18:53,209 --> 00:18:56,109
so I though t it just fell out of his pocket or something.

363
00:18:56,109 --> 00:18:57,909
Besides, after that,

364
00:18:57,909 --> 00:19:02,109
even on the surface of the swamp that Miwako drowned in,

365
00:19:02,109 --> 00:19:04,009
there was a ping pong ball.

366
00:19:04,009 --> 00:19:06,709
Balls, balls and more balls.

367
00:19:06,709 --> 00:19:10,409
So, the pearl is not a dying message.

368
00:19:10,409 --> 00:19:14,109
It seems to be a message that the culprit deliberately left behind!

369
00:19:15,409 --> 00:19:18,609
-Then, maybe... -That's the same too?

370
00:19:19,509 --> 00:19:23,209
We found it after Saki was taken to the hospital in the ambulance.

371
00:19:23,209 --> 00:19:26,809
It was rolling on the ground near the dog's grave, a marble!

372
00:19:26,809 --> 00:19:28,209
A marble?

373
00:19:28,209 --> 00:19:29,809
Do you have that with you now?

374
00:19:29,809 --> 00:19:33,709
We thought it was an offering, so we left it on the grave.

375
00:19:33,709 --> 00:19:36,509
Okay, we'll go take a look at that marble,

376
00:19:36,509 --> 00:19:38,709
so will you come with us too, officer?

377
00:19:38,709 --> 00:19:40,509
I've got some things I'd like to ask you too.

378
00:19:40,509 --> 00:19:42,009
Yeah.

379
00:19:42,009 --> 00:19:44,509
Kazuha and the rest of you, stay still and wait here!

380
00:19:44,509 --> 00:19:46,009
Ran, you too!

381
00:19:46,009 --> 00:19:48,109
What? We'll go with you too!

382
00:19:48,109 --> 00:19:50,109
We're the ones who found it, after all!

383
00:19:50,109 --> 00:19:51,609
You can come if you want!

384
00:19:51,609 --> 00:19:53,509
If you want to see the demon dog!

385
00:19:53,509 --> 00:19:55,909
I... I guess not.

386
00:19:55,909 --> 00:19:57,609
We'll wait here.

387
00:20:01,309 --> 00:20:04,509
I... I'm sorry to have barged in on you like this,

388
00:20:04,509 --> 00:20:07,009
and yet to be served dinner.

389
00:20:07,009 --> 00:20:09,209
No problem, don't worry about it.

390
00:20:09,209 --> 00:20:12,509
I wonder if Heiji and the others will be back before dawn?

391
00:20:12,509 --> 00:20:14,009
I wonder.

392
00:20:14,009 --> 00:20:16,909
More than that, we're really going to have it tough from now on

393
00:20:16,909 --> 00:20:21,709
since Saki was the one who made preparations

394
00:20:21,709 --> 00:20:24,609
and put things away most of the time.

395
00:20:26,909 --> 00:20:29,909
Can I help you with something?

396
00:20:29,909 --> 00:20:33,809
Then, could you go feed Hachi for me?

397
00:20:33,809 --> 00:20:35,609
Okay.

398
00:20:35,609 --> 00:20:39,709
I asked Takako and the others to do it, but they refused.

399
00:20:39,709 --> 00:20:41,609
Why?

400
00:20:41,609 --> 00:20:44,809
It seems that Takako is used to the dog and yet?

401
00:20:44,809 --> 00:20:49,309
Yes. It seems that she had a dog before she came here,

402
00:20:49,309 --> 00:20:51,109
so she knows a lot but...

403
00:20:51,109 --> 00:20:52,509
it seems she's got her hands full with

404
00:20:52,509 --> 00:20:55,109
making arrangements for the funeral and all.

405
00:20:55,109 --> 00:20:58,209
Tomoaki had been bitten by a dog in the past

406
00:20:58,209 --> 00:20:59,709
and really hates dogs!

407
00:20:59,709 --> 00:21:03,709
Since he's always jittery, Hachi really barks at him too.

408
00:21:03,709 --> 00:21:05,909
And Yoshiya's allergic to dogs.

409
00:21:05,909 --> 00:21:08,209
When near dogs, he can't stop sneezing

410
00:21:08,209 --> 00:21:10,809
and comes down with runny nose, he says.

411
00:21:10,809 --> 00:21:15,809
That's why it used to be Takako, Saki or I who fed the dog.

412
00:21:15,809 --> 00:21:18,809
-Could I ask you to do it for me? -Okay! Sure!

413
00:21:18,809 --> 00:21:21,909
Where's the doghouse?

414
00:21:21,909 --> 00:21:24,109
It's a bit far away.

415
00:21:24,109 --> 00:21:27,409
Far? Don't tell me that it's outside the house?

416
00:21:27,409 --> 00:21:30,109
Don't worry! It's towards the edge of house,

417
00:21:30,109 --> 00:21:34,109
but it's fenced in so even the demon dog can't go inside!

418
00:21:35,509 --> 00:21:36,709
Oh, I see.

419
00:21:43,409 --> 00:21:45,909
Boy, it sure is a large yard.

420
00:21:45,909 --> 00:21:47,509
Yes.

421
00:21:49,609 --> 00:21:51,909
Isn't that it, the doghouse?

422
00:21:51,909 --> 00:21:54,709
Right! Hachi's there too!

423
00:21:56,509 --> 00:21:59,809
Hachi! We brought you dinner!

424
00:22:01,609 --> 00:22:03,709
Eat it all now!

425
00:22:03,709 --> 00:22:06,109
-He's so cute! -Yes!

426
00:22:06,109 --> 00:22:09,109
It'd be nice if the demon dog is this way too.

427
00:22:15,409 --> 00:22:17,809
What's the matter?

428
00:22:20,809 --> 00:22:22,109
What's that?

429
00:22:22,109 --> 00:22:24,609
Isn't there something glowing over there?

430
00:22:24,609 --> 00:22:25,909
Yes.

431
00:23:58,309 --> 00:24:01,309
This place is full of books on magic!

432
00:24:01,309 --> 00:24:04,409
There's a magic circle drawn on the floor too.

433
00:24:04,409 --> 00:24:08,509
I'm sure that someone cast a curse on the dog here.

434
00:24:13,609 --> 00:24:16,509
The culprit will probably not get caught.

435
00:24:16,509 --> 00:24:19,809
After all we're going after a Black Magic Magician,

436
00:24:19,809 --> 00:24:22,009
who can curse a dog, you know?

437
00:24:22,009 --> 00:24:23,409
Next Conan,

438
00:24:23,409 --> 00:24:25,709
"Inubushi Castle, The Ablazed Demon Dog"

439
00:24:25,709 --> 00:24:27,709
"(Footprints Chapter)"

440
00:24:43,409 --> 00:24:45,809
Next Conan's Hint:

441
00:24:45,809 --> 00:24:47,609
"Onions"

442
00:24:47,609 --> 00:24:49,309
What will come out if you peel an onion?

443
00:24:49,309 --> 00:24:50,709
Nothing's going to come out.

444
00:24:50,709 --> 00:24:52,509
Tears are.

